.SH NAME
HTMLTrackElement \- HTMLTrackElement
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]HTMLTrackElement\f[B]\f[R] interface represents an HTML
\f[CR]<track>\f[R] element within the DOM.
This element can be used as a child of either \f[CR]<audio>\f[R] or
\f[CR]<video>\f[R] to specify a text track containing information such
as closed captions or subtitles.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]Inherits properties from its parent, \f[CI]HTMLElement\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]HTMLTrackElement.kind\f[R]
A string that reflects the \f[CR]kind\f[R] HTML attribute, indicating
how the text track is meant to be used.
Possible values are: \f[CR]subtitles\f[R], \f[CR]captions\f[R],
\f[CR]descriptions\f[R], \f[CR]chapters\f[R], or \f[CR]metadata\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]HTMLTrackElement.src\f[R]
A string that reflects the \f[CR]src\f[R] HTML attribute, indicating the
address of the text track data.
.TP
\f[B]HTMLTrackElement.srclang\f[R]
A string that reflects the \f[CR]srclang\f[R] HTML attribute, indicating
the language of the text track data.
.TP
\f[B]HTMLTrackElement.label\f[R]
A string that reflects the \f[CR]label\f[R] HTML attribute, indicating a
user\-readable title for the track.
.TP
\f[B]HTMLTrackElement.default\f[R]
A boolean value reflecting the \f[CR]default\f[R] attribute, indicating
that the track is to be enabled if the user\(cqs preferences do not
indicate that another track would be more appropriate.
