.SH EVENTS
\f[I]Inherits events from its parent, \f[CI]HTMLElement\f[I].\f[R]
.PP
Listen to these events using \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R] or by
assigning an event listener to the \f[CR]oneventname\f[R] property of
this interface:
.TP
\f[B]cuechange\f[R]
Sent when the underlying \f[CR]TextTrack\f[R] has changed the
currently\-presented cues.
This event is always sent to the \f[CR]TextTrack\f[R] but is
\f[I]also\f[R] sent to the \f[CR]HTMLTrackElement\f[R] if one is
associated with the track.
You may also use the \f[CR]oncuechange\f[R] event handler to establish a
handler for this event.
